<article>
    <h1>Nur&#xAD;tureS&#xAD;tars Build&#xAD;ing strength all round</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20201221/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-12-21"><time>2020-12-21</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE SMART PARENTING</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>Nur­tureS­tars Preschool, which be­gan op­er­a­tions in 2010, is one of the brands un­der the Kin­der­land Group. The chain, which is jointly man­aged with Safra, has six lo­ca­tions within Safra clubs and more than 600 chil­dren en­rolled.</p>
    <p>The fee from Jan 1 will be $760 for full-day childcare ser­vices, in ac­cor­dance with the part­ner-op­er­a­tor scheme. Kin­der­land Group has 14 cen­tres that will come un­der this scheme next year.</p>
    <p>WHAT THE PRE-SCHOOLS OF­FER</p>
    <p>A unique fea­ture of the Nur­tureS­tars cur­ricu­lum is its fo­cus on phys­i­cal ac­tiv­ity and men­tal de­vel­op­ment. Gen­eral man­ager Ng Kuan Wei says its ac­tive learn­ing cur­ricu­lum was de­vised with Jacpa, Ja­pan’s largest sports academy for pre-school­ers.</p>
    <p>Its fit­ness pro­grammes pay close at­ten­tion to the men­tal, phys­i­cal and emo­tional de­vel­op­ment of chil­dren through ex­er­cises aimed at im­prov­ing con­cen­tra­tion, mem­ory, dis­ci­pline, re­silience and team­work, notes Mr Ng.</p>
    <p>For ex­am­ple, chil­dren learn so­cial skills like team­work and re­silience when they cre­ate for­ma­tion line-ups as they have to train to per­form move­ments in sync.</p>
    <p>They also have vault­ing ex­er­cises, which are usu­ally done in gym­nas­tics. This builds up a child’s core mus­cle strength and con­fi­dence, says Mr Ng.</p>
    <p>Apart from phys­i­cal ac­tiv­ity, the cur­ricu­lum con­sists of six learn­ing ar­eas – aes­thet­ics and creative ex­pres­sion; dis­cov­ery of the world (science); lan­guage and lit­er­acy; mo­tor skills de­vel­op­ment; nu­mer­acy (math­e­mat­ics and cod­ing); and so­cial and emo­tional de­vel­op­ment.</p>
    <p>Chil­dren are also grad­u­ally ex­posed to tech toys and the fun­da­men­tals of cod­ing through a Play­Maker pro­gramme. They learn log­i­cal think­ing and team­work as they learn to con­trol and di­rect the move­ments of cod­ing ro­bots.</p>

